current matriculated students who have less than 60 units earned are encouraged to consult with an essc change of major advisor for the most up to date change of major information. the following steps are a quick overview.majors in the college of engineering are rigorous, so departments require specific coursework to be completed before their program plan is officially changed.you can attend a change of major workshop, view thetransition planning document [pdf] [pdf]for information about mandatory prerequisites, or meet with an essc advisor.note: if interested in civil engineering, please contact dr. olivia yipolivia.yip@sjsu.edufor the most up to date change of major eligibility requirements.if interested in computer or software engineering, pleasevisit the cmpe/se departments' faq pagefor eligibility information.apply during the semester in which final prerequisites are being completed. attention: if completing your prerequisites at another college:use our change of major online application during the open application window (openfor spring 2023 semester).if accepted to the major, you will be notified through your sjsu email. if admitted,of receiving your acceptance email, and the essc will work with the office of the registrar to officially change your major on your myprogress report.waiting for acceptance notices can make planning for the next term difficult or confusing. until your records are updated to the new major, you might not be able to register for major courses until the first week of courses or you will need to talk to the department for an add code.please be flexible and understand that you might not have the most ideal schedule your first semester in the new major. this is especially true if you're changing your major in the spring, as students are notified within two weeks of the start of the spring term.in the meantime, use the following planning tools to determine which courses you should register for:if you need additional help, please consider 